data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"## Prometheus Monitoring — Full Status Report\n\n**Overall: 50 targets UP, 4 targets DOWN, 0 active alerts.** The cluster is operating at **92.6% scrape availability** with **1,529 metrics** being collected across **6 scrape jobs**. Two OpenAgentic application pods and two Kubernetes infrastructure targets are unreachable.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Health Summary\n\n| Metric | Value | Status |\n|--------|------:|:------:|\n| **Targets UP** | 50 | ✅ |\n| **Targets DOWN** | 4 | ⚠️ |\n| **Firing Alerts** | 0 | ✅ |\n| **Pending Alerts** | 0 | ✅ |\n| **HTTP Request Rate (5m)** | 0.416 req/s | ✅ |\n| **Error Rate (5m)** | 0 | ✅ |\n| **Active Sessions** | 0 | ✅ |\n| **Total Metrics Available** | 1,529 | ✅ |\n| **Dropped Targets** | 478 | — |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scrape Target Status by Job\n\n| Job | UP | Down | Availability | Status |\n|-----|:--:|:----:|:------------:|:------:|\n| **dcgm-exporter** | 1 | 0 | 100% | ✅ |\n| **kube-state-metrics** | 0 | 1 | 0% | ❌ |\n| **kubernetes-apiservers** | 0 | 1 | 0% | ❌ |\n| **kubernetes-nodes** | 6 | 0 | 100% | ✅ |\n| **kubernetes-pods** | 27 | 2 | 93.1% | ⚠️ |\n| **kubernetes-service-endpoints** | 10 | 0 | 100% | ✅ |\n| **node-exporter** | 6 | 0 | 100% | ✅ |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Down Targets — Root Cause Analysis\n\n| Target | Endpoint | Error | Root Cause |\n|--------|----------|-------|------------|\n| **kube-state-metrics** | `kube-state-metrics.kube-system:8080` | HTTP 404 | Service is running but metrics endpoint not found — possible version mismatch or misconfigured path |\n| **kubernetes-apiservers** | `10.2.10.131:6443` | HTTP 403 Forbidden | Prometheus ServiceAccount lacks RBAC to scrape the API server |\n| **openagentic-code-manager** | `10.42.5.19:8080` | Connection refused | Pod `openagentic-code-manager-7469b5f78d-d6kqx` in `agentic-dev` is not accepting connections |\n| **openagentic-openagentic-synth** | `10.42.2.37:8090` | Connection refused | Pod `openagentic-openagentic-synth-5b6dcbb7dc-ms96j` in `agentic-dev` is not accepting connections |\n\n> [!WARNING]\n> The **code-manager** and **openagentic-synth** failures are persistent — these same two pods were down in previous audits. This indicates a chronic issue, not a transient restart.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Monitored Services Inventory\n\n### Kubernetes Cluster Nodes (6/6 ✅)\n\n| Node | Architecture | OS | Kernel |\n|------|:------------:|:--:|--------|\n| **dalek** | amd64 (Intel) | Ubuntu 22.04 | 6.8.0-90-generic |\n| **k8a** (control-plane) | arm64 (ARM) | Ubuntu 24.04 | 6.8.0-1044-raspi |\n| **k8b** | arm64 (ARM) | Ubuntu 24.04 | 6.8.0-1044-raspi |\n| **k8c** | arm64 (ARM) | Ubuntu 24.04 | 6.8.0-1044-raspi |\n| **k8d** | arm64 (ARM) | Ubuntu 24.04 | 6.8.0-1044-raspi |\n| **k8e** | arm64 (ARM) | Ubuntu 24.04 | 6.8.0-1044-raspi |\n\n### OpenAgentic Platform Services (`agentic-dev` namespace)\n\n| Service | Pod | Port | Status |\n|---------|-----|:----:|:------:|\n| **API** | `openagentic-api-6ffdf956b5-6gztf` | 8000 | ✅ UP |\n| **MCP Proxy** | `openagentic-mcp-proxy-66c57b9b95-g9w5f` | 8080 | ✅ UP |\n| **CrewAI** | `openagentic-crewai-c9b9855c-k6lpc` | 3200 | ✅ UP |\n| **LangGraph** | `openagentic-langgraph-6f76845bdd-pdkvz` | 3100 | ✅ UP |\n| **Code Manager** | `openagentic-code-manager-7469b5f78d-d6kqx` | 8080 | ❌ DOWN |\n| **OAT Executor** | `openagentic-openagentic-synth-5b6dcbb7dc-ms96j` | 8090 | ❌ DOWN |\n\n### Infrastructure Services\n\n| Service | Namespace | Instances | Status |\n|---------|-----------|:---------:|:------:|\n| **Node Exporter** | monitoring-stack | 6/6 | ✅ |\n| **Promtail** (log shipper) | monitoring-stack | 6/6 | ✅ |\n| **Prometheus** | monitoring-stack | 1/1 | ✅ |\n| **Loki** (logs) | monitoring-stack | 1/1 | ✅ |\n| **CoreDNS** | kube-system | 1/1 | ✅ |\n| **cert-manager** | cert-manager | 3/3 | ✅ |\n| **MetalLB** (controller + speakers) | metallb-system | 7/7 | ✅ |\n| **Envoy Gateway** | envoy-gateway-system | 1/1 | ✅ |\n| **GPU Operator** | gpu-operator | 1/1 | ✅ |\n| **DCGM Exporter** (GPU metrics) | gpu-operator | 1/1 | ✅ |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Metrics Coverage Summary\n\n| Category | Metric Count | Coverage Area |\n|----------|:----------:|---------------|\n| **node_*** | 325 | Hardware, OS, filesystem, network per node |\n| **prometheus_*** | 221 | Prometheus internal health and performance |\n| **apiserver_*** | 155 | Kubernetes API server request/latency/admission |\n| **go_*** | 143 | Go runtime (GC, memory, goroutines) per service |\n| **kubelet_*** | 109 | Container runtime, pod lifecycle, volumes |\n| **coredns_*** | 44 | DNS resolution, caching, forwarding |\n| **kube_*** | 38 | Cluster-level resource allocation |\n| **scheduler_*** | 37 | Pod scheduling decisions and latency |\n| **kubeproxy_*** | 27 | Network proxying, iptables, conntrack |\n| **nodejs_*** | 24 | Node.js runtime (Flowise/Loki) |\n| **promtail_*** | 20 | Log pipeline throughput and failures |\n| **http_*** | 16 | Application HTTP request/response metrics |\n| **DCGM_*** | 15 | GPU utilization, temperature, memory |\n| **metallb_*** | 14 | Load balancer address allocation |\n| **loki_*** | 14 | Log storage, ingestion, queries |\n| **certmanager_*** | 11 | TLS certificate lifecycle |\n| **crewai_*** | 9 | CrewAI agent execution and LLM calls |\n| **langgraph_*** | 9 | LangGraph workflow execution and LLM calls |\n| **chat_*** | 4 | Chat message counts and response times |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Recommendations\n\n| # | Action | Priority | Impact |\n|---|--------|:--------:|:------:|\n| 1 | **Investigate `openagentic-code-manager`** — persistent connection refused on `:8080`. Check pod logs and restart policy. This is a recurring failure. | **P1** | High |\n| 2 | **Investigate `openagentic-openagentic-synth`** — persistent connection refused on `:8090`. Same chronic pattern as code-manager. | **P1** | High |\n| 3 | **Fix kube-state-metrics** — HTTP 404 suggests the `/metrics` path changed or the deployment is misconfigured in `kube-system`. | **P2** | Medium |\n| 4 | **Fix API server scrape RBAC** — Prometheus gets 403 Forbidden from `10.2.10.131:6443`. Create a ClusterRoleBinding granting `get` on `/metrics`. | **P2** | Medium |\n| 5 | **Configure alert rules** — Zero firing/pending alerts with 4 targets down means alerting rules are missing or insufficient. Add `TargetDown` alerts. | **P2** | High |\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> The absence of any firing alerts despite 4 targets being down indicates a **monitoring gap**. Alert rules should be configured for `up == 0` conditions, especially for the OpenAgentic application services."}

